    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the FEA model for the non-cannulated compression-bending COU based on satisfactory output comparison results (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs, N=11 constructs, two laboratories) and assessed factors meeting or exceeding required levels in 11 of 13 V&V 40 factors. The Test conditions factor fell below required level (achieved 2, required 3) and is acknowledged as a gap; however, the team judged the single-condition validation sufficient for the static compression-bending submission context. Numerical solver error and Use error were not assessed and were characterized as beyond scope for this submission cycle, with the expectation that these will be addressed in a subsequent revision. The overall credibility profile was deemed adequate for a Medium assurance level decision at modelRiskLevel 3.",
